Collection.Description: Amount of key/value pairs in this Collection.
Main interaction point of this Collection.
Params: {*} Key Specifies an address for this value.
{*} Value A value to be inserted at the key of this document.

Collection.Description: Main interaction point of this Collection.
Params: {*} Key Specifies a key to erase from this Collection.

Collection.Description: Main interaction point of this Collection.
Params: {*} Key Specifies a key to fetch from this Collection.
Collection.Returns: {*} If found, the element at the address of the key.

Collection.Description: Main interaction point of this Collection.
Params: {*} Key Specifies a key to see if it exists.
Collection.Returns: {Boolean} A boolean value to indicate whether this element exists.

Collection.Description: Creates an ordered array of the values of this Collection.
Collection.Returns: {Array} Array of values in this Collection.

Collection.Description: Creates an ordered array of the keys of this Collection.
Collection.Returns: {Array} Array of keys in this Collection.

Collection.Description: Creates an ordered object of all the entries of this Collection.
Collection.Returns: {Object} Object of the key/value pairs in this Collection.

Collection.Description: Obtains the first value(s) from this Collection. Starting from the end if a negative amount is provided.
Params: {Number} [Amount] Amount of values to obtain from the beginning.
Collection.Returns: {*|Collection} A single value, or a new Collection of entries if there's an amount provided.

Collection.Description: Obtains the last value(s) from this Collection. Starting from the beginning if a negative amount is provided.
Params: {Number} [Amount] Amount of values to obtain from the end.
Collection.Returns: {*|Collection} A single value, or a new Collection of entries if there's an amount provided.

Collection.Description: Searches for a specific item where the given function returns a truthy value.
Params: {Function} Fn Function used to test iterating elements with.
Collection.Returns: {*} Returns the value of the element found.

Collection.Description: Identical to `Array.filter()`, but returns a Collection instead of an array.
Params: {Function} Fn Function used to test the iterating elements with.

Collection.Description: Removes entries that satisfy the provided filter function.
Params: {Function} Fn Function used to test the iterating elements with.
Collection.Returns: {Number} Returns the number of deleted entries.

Collection.Description: Partitions the Collection into two (when returning boolean values) or more Collections. If a boolean was given, the first Collection contains the items that passed the test.
Params: {Function} Fn Function used to test the iterating elements with.
{Number} [Length] Expected length, and the length of the array of Collections to return.

Collection.Description: Checks if there is an item that exists that passes a test.
Params: {Function} Fn Function used to test iterating elements with.
Collection.Returns: {Boolean} Returns a boolean based on whether or not an element was found.

Collection.Description: Checks whether all the elements in this Collection pass the test.
Params: {Function} Fn Function used to test iterating elements with.
Collection.Returns: {Boolean} Returns a boolean based on whether or not all elements pass the test.

Collection.Description: Provides an identical, deep copy of this Collection.
